Class AbstractFloatIterator

java.lang.Object
it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.floats.AbstractFloatIterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
FloatIterator, Iterator<Float>, PrimitiveIterator<Float,FloatConsumer>
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractFloatBidirectionalIterator, FloatBigListIterators.AbstractIndexBasedBigIterator, FloatIterators.AbstractIndexBasedIterator
public abstract class AbstractFloatIterator extends Object implements FloatIterator
An abstract class facilitating the creation of type-specific iterators.
API Notes:
Up to version 8.5.0, this class was deprecated as abstract methods were turned into default methods of the type-specific interface. Now the class hosts finalized versions of default delegating methods such as FloatIterator.forEachRemaining(it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.floats.FloatConsumer).
